<div id="wb_element_instance641" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#e3b709;"><strong>BARILOCHE</strong></span></h3>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Bariloche is the most visited city in Patagonia and third nationally tourist destination. It is the most populous city in the Argentina Patagonian Andes. It is located in the Nahuel Huapi National Park, in the southwestern province of Rio Negro, near the Andes, on the southern shore of Lake Nahuel Huapi. Its natural reserves, including lakes, forests and mountains, and their outstanding ski resorts are the main attraction and economic livelihood of this city. The city has been considered by some sources as the second ski destination worldwide.</span></strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#d6c90f;"><strong>BARILOCHE 4 days, 3 nights</strong></span></h3>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">The program includes the followind services:</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">* In Bariloche: Accommodation at the chosen hotel with breakfast.<br>
* Transfers Airport / Hotel / Airport.<br>
* Circuito Chico Excursion. ( a short tour of the nearby areas)<br>
* Golf Day</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Not Included:<br>
- Domestic or International flights<br>
- Entrances to National Parks</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Day 1: BUENOS AIRES / BARILOCHE</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">In the Buenos Aires City Airport, you will take a flight heading for Los Andes Mountain Rage. When you arrive in Bariloche you could immediately see Cathedral Mountain.Transfers to the chosen hotel. The rest of the day is free. According to your flight time you could take an excursion or any other activity. For example, in the Circuito Chico, you'll find the most wonderful views, combination of mountains, lakes and changing colors depending on the season of the year. If that day you decide not to go on any excursion, the San Carlos de Bariloche's Civic and Commercial Center will offer you a lots of possibilities with an incomparable view of the Nahuel Huapi Lake. Lodging.</span></strong><br><br>
 </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Day 2: BARILOCHE – GOLF DAY</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Breakfast. Golf Day. Transfers included. At night, return to hotel. Lodging.</span></strong><br>
 </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Day 3: BARILOCHE</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Breakfast. Free day, we have thought up something special for you: Victoria Island and the Arrayanes Forest. You can´t miss it!: sailing on the deep blue waters of the Nahuel HuapiLake and visiting this unique forest in the world. Or also sailing to Puerto Blest and Los Cántaros Cascade that won`t be less incredible than any other excursion. At night we suggest your tasting some of the regional delicacies, as the smoked trout<br>
(trucha ahumada, a type of lake fish). Then, you´ll return to your hotel.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong style="background-color: transparent;"><span style="color:#000000;">Day 4: BARILOCHE / BUENOS AIRES</span></strong></h2>

<p> </p>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Breakfast. Transfer to the Airport of San Carlos de Bariloche, with your hands full of chocolates as it almost always happens. Arrival at the Aiport of Buenos Aires City. Transfer to the chosen hotel.</span></strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong style="background-color: transparent;"><span style="color:#000000;">Golf Day &amp; Car Rental in Bariloche</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color:#000000;">The program includes the following services:<br>
One day Car Rental of a Compact Car with 200 km. Allowance. Car Insurance Franchise included. Green fee 18 holes. Caddie included. Gratuities not included.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Single u$s 251.-<br>
Double u$s 178.-</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="color:#000000;">Golf Courses suggested in Bariloche:<br>
Llao Llao: http://www.llaollao.com/ing/golf.asp<br>
Arelauquen: http://www.arelauquen.com/sitio/</span></strong></h1>

